definition:
πενθέω, -ῶ 
 [in LXX chiefly for אָבַל ;] 
to mourn (for), lament; 
   (a) intrans. : Mat.5:4 (5) Mat.9:15, 1Co.5:2; π. καὶ κλαίειν, Mat.16:10, Luk.6:25, Jas.4:9, Rev.18:15, 19; before ἐπί, with accusative, Rev.18:11; 
   (b) trans., with accusative, 2Co.12:21.†
 SYN.: see: θρηνέω  (AS)
